"use strict";(self.webpackChunksfit_delivery_knowledge_hub=self.webpackChunksfit_delivery_knowledge_hub||[]).push([[301],{10:e=>{e.exports=JSON.parse('{"blogPosts":[{"id":"hub_is_now_live","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/hub_is_now_live","editUrl":"https://github.com/SFITDelivery/SFITDelivery-KnowledgeHub/tree/main/blog/2026-04-15-SFITDelivery-KnowledgeHub_Is_Now_Live/index.md","source":"@site/blog/2026-04-15-SFITDelivery-KnowledgeHub_Is_Now_Live/index.md","title":"SFITDelivery Knowledge Hub Is Live","description":"The SFITDelivery Knowledge Hub is now live at sfdevops.info and fully open source on GitHub.","date":"2026-04-15T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"April 15, 2026","tags":[{"label":"Salesforce","permalink":"/blog/tags/salesforce"},{"label":"DevOps","permalink":"/blog/tags/dev-ops"},{"label":"Open Source","permalink":"/blog/tags/open-source"},{"label":"Launch","permalink":"/blog/tags/launch"}],"readingTime":2.375,"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[{"name":"Stanislav Dudkov","title":"Project Lead & Knowledge Curator","url":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/stanislavd2269/","imageURL":"https://github.com/d2269.png","key":"d2269"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"hub_is_now_live","title":"SFITDelivery Knowledge Hub Is Live","authors":["d2269"],"tags":["Salesforce","DevOps","Open Source","Launch"]},"unlisted":false,"nextItem":{"title":"A section on environment management has been added","permalink":"/blog/environments_section_added"}},"content":"The **SFITDelivery Knowledge Hub** is now live at [sfdevops.info](https://sfdevops.info) and fully open source on [GitHub](https://github.com/SFITDelivery/SFITDelivery-KnowledgeHub).\\n\\nThis launch turns nearly four years of notes, templates, and delivery lessons into a public knowledge base for Salesforce teams. The goal is simple: make practical DevOps and Delivery Management guidance easier to find, reuse, and improve. Too many teams still rebuild the same release process, branching model, deployment checklist, and environment controls from scratch. This hub is meant to help with that.\\n\\n## What You Can Read Today\\nThe site already includes practical content across the core areas of Salesforce delivery:\\n- **Roles and responsibilities** for DevOps specialists and Delivery Managers\\n- **Git strategies** for Salesforce teams, including Trunk-Based Development, Git Flow, Org Branch, parallel releases, feature branches, and hotfix paths\\n- **Release management** topics such as planning, release on demand, incremental releases, large-scale delivery, and anti-patterns\\n- **Salesforce deployment** fundamentals, metadata delivery options, test execution, destructive changes, Quick Deploy, and packages\\n- **Delivery strategies** such as phased rollouts, dark launches, blue-green deployment, big bang, and A/B testing\\n- **Environment management** and operational controls, including monitoring, backups, debug logs, Event Monitoring, and Security Health Check\\n- **Tooling guidance** comparing platforms such as Copado, Gearset, and Salesforce DevOps Center\\n\\nThe strongest content today is intentionally practical and Salesforce-specific: branching, release process, deployment, environments, and operational reliability. This is not generic DevOps advice rewritten for a different platform. It is focused on the decisions Salesforce delivery teams actually make.\\n\\n## What Comes Next\\nThis is only the first public release. The roadmap continues into Delivery Management, process maturity, prioritization, quality control, audit, automation, and AI-assisted workflows for Salesforce teams.\\n\\nYou can follow planned and upcoming content on the [Knowledge Hub Content Board](https://github.com/users/SFITDelivery/projects/1).\\n\\n## Who This Is For\\nIf you work in Salesforce delivery as a DevOps engineer, Delivery Manager, release manager, architect, admin, or tech lead, this project is for you.\\n\\nStart with the [introduction](/docs/intro), explore the sections that match your current challenge, and use the repository as a practical reference point for building better delivery processes.\\n\\n## Contribute\\nThis is a living knowledge base, not a finished book. If you have a better branching model, a stronger rollout checklist, a deployment edge case, or a lesson learned from a real project, contributions are welcome.\\n\\nOpen an issue, suggest an article, submit a pull request, or share the hub with your team. The more practical experience we can capture, the more useful this project becomes.\\n\\n## Meet in Berlin\\nIf you\'ll be in Berlin on May 8, 2026, I\'ll also be speaking at [Wir sind Ohana](https://wirsindohana.de/agenda/) about optimizing releases for Salesforce projects in a session called _Small or Large, Often or Rare? How to Optimize Releases_. It is closely connected to the same problems this Knowledge Hub is built to solve, so feel free to join the session and say hello."},{"id":"environments_section_added","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/environments_section_added","editUrl":"https://github.com/SFITDelivery/SFITDelivery-KnowledgeHub/tree/main/blog/2025-04-05-added_environments_management_section/index.md","source":"@site/blog/2025-04-05-added_environments_management_section/index.md","title":"A section on environment management has been added","description":"Work on an important section dedicated to monitoring and managing Salesforce environments has been completed.","date":"2025-04-05T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"April 5, 2025","tags":[{"label":"DevOps","permalink":"/blog/tags/dev-ops"},{"label":"DM","permalink":"/blog/tags/dm"},{"label":"Update","permalink":"/blog/tags/update"}],"readingTime":0.825,"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[{"name":"Stanislav Dudkov","title":"Project Lead & Knowledge Curator","url":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/stanislavd2269/","imageURL":"https://github.com/d2269.png","key":"d2269"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"environments_section_added","title":"A section on environment management has been added","authors":["d2269"],"tags":["DevOps","DM","Update"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"SFITDelivery Knowledge Hub Is Live","permalink":"/blog/hub_is_now_live"},"nextItem":{"title":"The delivery strategie section has been added.","permalink":"/blog/delivery_strategie_section_added"}},"content":"Work on an important section dedicated to [monitoring and managing Salesforce environments](/docs/category/enviroments) has been completed. \\n\\n### The following articles have been added so far:\\n**Backup:**\\n- **Data Backup** \u2013 strategies for data backup and tool selection  \\n- **Metadata Backup** \u2013 how and why to back up your environment\u2019s configuration\\n\\n**Salesforce Monitoring:**\\n- **System Overview** \u2013 tracking system resources  \\n- **Debug Logs** \u2013 debugging Apex errors and more  \\n- **Apex Exception Email** \u2013 automatic failure notifications in code  \\n- **Event Monitoring, Real-Time Event Monitoring** \u2013 auditing events and activity  \\n- **Security Health Check** \u2013 evaluating and managing environment security  \\n\\nThe articles cover not only the built-in Salesforce tools but also practical advice on automation, CI/CD, and security compliance.  \\nWith these materials, you\u2019ll be able to efficiently monitor the state of your Salesforce environment, quickly detect issues, and proactively prevent incidents.\\n\\nExplore the new section, apply best practices, and ensure the stability and security of your Salesforce projects!\\n\\n**Got something to add? Suggest edits or new articles!**"},{"id":"delivery_strategie_section_added","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/delivery_strategie_section_added","editUrl":"https://github.com/SFITDelivery/SFITDelivery-KnowledgeHub/tree/main/blog/2025-02-22-added_delivery_strategies_management_section/index.md","source":"@site/blog/2025-02-22-added_delivery_strategies_management_section/index.md","title":"The delivery strategie section has been added.","description":"A new section on change Delivery Strategies has been added to the knowledge base. Now, detailed materials on key deployment methods are available to help minimize risks and improve system stability.","date":"2025-02-22T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"February 22, 2025","tags":[{"label":"DevOps","permalink":"/blog/tags/dev-ops"},{"label":"DM","permalink":"/blog/tags/dm"},{"label":"Update","permalink":"/blog/tags/update"}],"readingTime":0.575,"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[{"name":"Stanislav Dudkov","title":"Project Lead & Knowledge Curator","url":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/stanislavd2269/","imageURL":"https://github.com/d2269.png","key":"d2269"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"delivery_strategie_section_added","title":"The delivery strategie section has been added.","authors":["d2269"],"tags":["DevOps","DM","Update"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"A section on environment management has been added","permalink":"/blog/environments_section_added"},"nextItem":{"title":"The deployment management section has been updated.","permalink":"/blog/deployment_management_section_added"}},"content":"A new section on change [Delivery Strategies](/docs/category/delivery-strategies) has been added to the knowledge base. Now, detailed materials on key deployment methods are available to help minimize risks and improve system stability.\\nWhat\'s New?\\n- **Fundamentals of Delivery Strategies** \u2013 How to choose the optimal deployment method\\n- **Phased Rollouts** \u2013 Step-by-step implementation to reduce risks\\n- **Dark Launches** \u2013 Deploying without user visibility\\n- **Blue-Green Deployment** \u2013 Minimizing downtime and enabling quick rollbacks\\n- **Big Bang Deployment** \u2013 Full release in one go and its risks\\n- **A/B Testing** \u2013 Experimenting to enhance user experience\\n\\nThese materials will help DevOps engineers, Delivery managers, and anyone involved in system changes to manage deployments efficiently and safely."},{"id":"deployment_management_section_added","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/deployment_management_section_added","editUrl":"https://github.com/SFITDelivery/SFITDelivery-KnowledgeHub/tree/main/blog/2024-12-08-added_deployment_management_section/index.md","source":"@site/blog/2024-12-08-added_deployment_management_section/index.md","title":"The deployment management section has been updated.","description":"Basic articles have been added to the deployment management section.","date":"2024-12-08T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"December 8, 2024","tags":[{"label":"DevOps","permalink":"/blog/tags/dev-ops"},{"label":"DM","permalink":"/blog/tags/dm"},{"label":"Update","permalink":"/blog/tags/update"}],"readingTime":0.89,"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[{"name":"Stanislav Dudkov","title":"Project Lead & Knowledge Curator","url":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/stanislavd2269/","imageURL":"https://github.com/d2269.png","key":"d2269"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"deployment_management_section_added","title":"The deployment management section has been updated.","authors":["d2269"],"tags":["DevOps","DM","Update"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"The delivery strategie section has been added.","permalink":"/blog/delivery_strategie_section_added"},"nextItem":{"title":"The release management section has been updated.","permalink":"/blog/release_management_section_added"}},"content":"Basic articles have been added to the [deployment management section](/docs/category/salesforce-deployment).  \\nIn this section, you will find materials that will help optimize deployment processes, and improve system stability.\\n\\nThe section includes articles on the following key topics:\\n- **Basics of Deployment Management**: Understanding the differences between release and deployment stages to minimize risks and improve planning.\\n- **Process Automation**: Fundamental principles and approaches to automation for increased reliability and efficiency.\\n- **Metadata Deployment Approaches**: Choosing between full and partial deployment to optimize resources and enhance control.\\n- **Testing During Deployment**: Running tests to ensure high quality and system stability.\\n- **Removing Outdated Components**: Recommendations for implementing destructive changes to maintain order and relevance in the system.\\n- **Quick Deploy**: Leveraging accelerated deployment for critical changes.\\n- **Version Management**: Utilizing modular approaches and Salesforce packages to simplify updates and improve control.\\n- **Quality Control**: Using test coverage matrices for transparent analysis and quality improvement.\\n\\nThis section will become a valuable tool for teams aiming to optimize development and deployment processes in Salesforce. If you\'d like to contribute, join the project!"},{"id":"release_management_section_added","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/release_management_section_added","editUrl":"https://github.com/SFITDelivery/SFITDelivery-KnowledgeHub/tree/main/blog/2024-08-26-added_release_management_section/index.md","source":"@site/blog/2024-08-26-added_release_management_section/index.md","title":"The release management section has been updated.","description":"Basic articles have been added to the release management section.","date":"2024-08-26T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"August 26, 2024","tags":[{"label":"DevOps","permalink":"/blog/tags/dev-ops"},{"label":"DM","permalink":"/blog/tags/dm"},{"label":"Update","permalink":"/blog/tags/update"}],"readingTime":0.26,"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[{"name":"Stanislav Dudkov","title":"Project Lead & Knowledge Curator","url":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/stanislavd2269/","imageURL":"https://github.com/d2269.png","key":"d2269"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"release_management_section_added","title":"The release management section has been updated.","authors":["d2269"],"tags":["DevOps","DM","Update"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"The deployment management section has been updated.","permalink":"/blog/deployment_management_section_added"},"nextItem":{"title":"Adding articles and updating the structure.","permalink":"/blog/git-and-roles-and-structure"}},"content":"Basic articles have been added to the [release management section](/docs/category/release).  \\nThe articles contain information on methodology and practical advice on release management, with a separate note dedicated to [HotFix](/docs/Practices_and_Processes/02_01_Release/02_01_04_HotFix). [Anti-patterns](/docs/Practices_and_Processes/02_01_Release/02_01_99_Anti_patterns) can help conduct a quick, superficial review of the project\'s release management processes, allowing for the identification of common mistakes and shortcomings."},{"id":"git-and-roles-and-structure","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/git-and-roles-and-structure","editUrl":"https://github.com/SFITDelivery/SFITDelivery-KnowledgeHub/tree/main/blog/2024-08-12-added_git_and_roles/index.md","source":"@site/blog/2024-08-12-added_git_and_roles/index.md","title":"Adding articles and updating the structure.","description":"The portal structure has been modified for easier navigation.","date":"2024-08-12T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"August 12, 2024","tags":[{"label":"DevOps","permalink":"/blog/tags/dev-ops"},{"label":"DM","permalink":"/blog/tags/dm"},{"label":"Update","permalink":"/blog/tags/update"}],"readingTime":0.16,"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[{"name":"Stanislav Dudkov","title":"Project Lead & Knowledge Curator","url":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/stanislavd2269/","imageURL":"https://github.com/d2269.png","key":"d2269"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"git-and-roles-and-structure","title":"Adding articles and updating the structure.","authors":["d2269"],"tags":["DevOps","DM","Update"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"The release management section has been updated.","permalink":"/blog/release_management_section_added"},"nextItem":{"title":"Welcome","permalink":"/blog/welcome"}},"content":"The portal structure has been modified for easier navigation.  \\nArticles on [Roles](/docs/Roles/) and [Git Management](/docs/category/git), including descriptions of strategies and comparisons, have been added.\\nArticles on other topics are currently being created."},{"id":"welcome","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/welcome","editUrl":"https://github.com/SFITDelivery/SFITDelivery-KnowledgeHub/tree/main/blog/2024-01-01-welcome/index.md","source":"@site/blog/2024-01-01-welcome/index.md","title":"Welcome","description":"DevOps and Delivery practices are underdeveloped in Salesforce projects.","date":"2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"January 1, 2024","tags":[{"label":"hello","permalink":"/blog/tags/hello"},{"label":"DevOps","permalink":"/blog/tags/dev-ops"},{"label":"DM","permalink":"/blog/tags/dm"}],"readingTime":0.48,"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[{"name":"Stanislav Dudkov","title":"Project Lead & Knowledge Curator","url":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/stanislavd2269/","imageURL":"https://github.com/d2269.png","key":"d2269"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"welcome","title":"Welcome","authors":["d2269"],"tags":["hello","DevOps","DM"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Adding articles and updating the structure.","permalink":"/blog/git-and-roles-and-structure"}},"content":"DevOps and Delivery practices are underdeveloped in Salesforce projects. \\nSmall projects often do not integrate these roles with the existing ones on the project, such as developers.\\nLarge projects turn to off-the-shelf products.\\nAll of this leads to suboptimal solutions, or pitfalls laid at the foundation of the project.\\n\\nThis resource is created for sharing and accumulating experience and best DevOps and Delivery practices within Salesforce and cross-projects.\\nHere, you will find documentation and technical solutions.\\n\\nPlease feel free to propose your changes/solutions/edits - this is an open project.\\n\\nLet\'s make this world a better place!"}]}')}}]);